headline: CrowdStrike price target raised to $415 from $372 at Goldman Sachs
summary: Goldman Sachs analyst Gabriela Borges raised the firm’s price target on CrowdStrike (CRWD) to $415 from $372 and keeps a Buy rating on the shares as the firm introduces its FY28 EPS forecast and rolls valuation forward from FY27. Given industry growth and CrowdStrike’s ongoing growth in its go to market team, the firm sees a scenario where net new annual recurring revenue is 17% above the Street for Q3 of FY26 through Q2 of FY27, the analyst tells investors. headline: Palo Alto Networks Just Went Through a Stock Split. Time to Buy?
summary: Palo Alto Networks' (NASDAQ: PANW) stock price may look a bit cheaper than it used to.  In the past, stock splits have been a kick-start for some stocks to go on monster runs.  For Palo Alto, the stock split hasn't done much so far.
